# Ghostty configuration (managed by workspace)

# Make Shift+Enter insert a newline in TUI apps (pi, Claude Code, etc.).
# By default Ghostty sends `[27;2;13~` for Shift+Enter, which these apps do
# not treat as a newline. Sending `\n` makes pi receive it as ctrl+j, which
# pi already maps to `tui.input.newLine`.
keybind = shift+enter=text:"\n"
